  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/3420",
  "title": "fix(InstantSearch): remove event listeners",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\nWe recently updated the `dispose` function to set the `helper` to `null`. It's indeed the right approach but it might happen that a `render` occurs after the `dispose` e.g `start` → `dispose` right after the start. The search is async so the render is called after we set the helper to null and it throws an error. To avoid this issue we have to remove the listeners on the helper before we lose his reference.",
